  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nAs I was reclaiming my ENS name `rachel.stateofus.eth` on the 18/11/19 nightly, I ran into a couple of small snags:\n\n1. The '->' button to trigger the transaction is very, very slow to respond. I tapped on it many times before the bottom sheet finally appeared.\n\n2. When the bottom sheet did appear, it loaded with this `Invalid number` error.\n\n![IMG_5953](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/69047955-41de9d80-09f4-11ea-9d6d-8bc9e93aaeef.PNG)\n\n3. After I signed and saw the confirmation screen, the contract interaction bottom sheet remained open and the `Invalid number` appeared again. I also had to tap the `Cancel` button multiple times to make it go away.\n\n![IMG_5956](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/15470435/69047962-460abb00-09f4-11ea-8e5d-00db8dd4ff19.PNG)\n\n4. ([separate issue](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/8837)) The system `Save password` option came up while I was trying to close the bottom sheet again. \n\n#### Expected behavior\n\n- Do not allow user to \"Show my ENS username in chats\" unless the setting Tx is mined. It should be grayed out if the Tx is not yet confirmed.\n- Buttons respond on first tap.\n- No 'invalid number' error.\n- Bottom sheet disappears once Tx has been signed. This should be fixed by preventing user from tapping button and triggering multiple Txs.\n\n#### Acceptance Criteria\n\nSee above.\n\n### Reproduction\n\n- In ENS flow, enter a name you already own and follow instructions.\n\n### Additional Information\n\n- Status version: Nightly\n- Operating System: iOS 13.1.3",
